.TH "tty_port_register_device_attr" 9 "tty_port_register_device_attr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_port_register_device_attr \- register tty device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct device *" tty_port_register_device_attr
.BI "(struct tty_port *port "  ","
.BI "struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "unsigned index "  ","
.BI "struct device *device "  ","
.BI "void *drvdata "  ","
.BI "const struct attribute_group **attr_grp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
tty_port of the device
.IP "driver" 12
tty_driver for this device
.IP "index" 12
index of the tty
.IP "device" 12
parent if exists, otherwise NULL
.IP "drvdata" 12
Driver data to be set to device.
.IP "attr_grp" 12
Attribute group to be set on device.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It is the same as tty_register_device_attr except the provided \fIport\fP is
linked to a concrete tty specified by \fIindex\fP. Use this or tty_port_install
(or both). Call tty_port_link_device as a last resort.
